Commit Message: CACert platform now seems to work
IDN domains seem to be working
Added README and excluded html files by gitignore
Sequential download of landing pages of rules. Replaced 're' with 'regex' since 're' sucks for many regexes that should work.
Added 'regex' module source and note about 'regex' in README.
Excluding wildcard domains from landing pages
Absolutizing relative location on HTTP 301/302 redirects.
Removed unused imports
Fixed handling redirects to also replace GET parameters when resolving relative path starting with slash. Implemented early detection of redirect loops via remembering URLs already fetched.
Fixed relative->absolute URL translation to conform to RFC 3986.
Fixed metrics to work for empty strings. Common abstract class for metrics.
Added missing continue that broke HTTP redirect following
Applying platform from rulesets when checking certchain from transformed page, including 301/302 redirects.
Explicit cleanup of pycurl objects
Note about Varnish/proxy_html bug
README formatting
Storing originating filename of ruleset
Workaround for numbered capture groups: only one digit considered as group number.
Corrected skipping of default-off rulesets
Targets with leading * are skipped when looking for URLs to test.
Selection of metric and threshold read from config.
Skipping targets with wildcards in Ruleset.uniqueTargetFQDNs
Lowered debug level of few messages so that logs won't be cluttered as much in non-debug scenario
Error logging with
Added symlinks for 'firefox' and 'chromium' platforms, for now considered to be identical with 'default' platform
Automatic loading of platform certdirs instead of having them hardcoded. Added user agent and CURL verbose options.
HTTP 400 culprit found - it's NSS
Note about CAPATH, openssl and Windows
Scanning and comparing URLs obtained from rulesets in threads.
Features/shortcomings in README
Added license
ASCII art explaining matching in the rule trie.
Comment clarification on the wildcards in target element in rulesets

Rename the T�rktrust certs to shorten their filenames

(Otherwise, they exceed the limits on some filesystems)
More files to rename
c_rehash-ed renamed certs for openssl
First phase of 'transvalid cert transitive closure' - added certs from Firefox

Commit Message: README points to transvalid tarball instead of deleted directory
Preparing for refactoring - minimized try/finally scope of curl fetching in HTTPFetcher
Refactoring - removed all non-curl related stuff from innermost try/final curl fetch block in HTTPFetcher
Extracted curl fetching into static method. Two new picklable classes for marshalling in/out args for fetcher to be used in subprocess invocation later.
Subprocess HTTP(S) fetching core.
Finished fetching in subprocesses
Documentation on threading race conditions
Added config option 'static_ca_path' to override using platform CA path based on platform attribute from ruleset file
Note about subprocess side effect for the CURL+NSS SNI bug
Note about SSL lib quirks
Setting fetch_in_subprocess to True as default - looks like it's a great prevention of many bugs in dependent libraries.
Final note on configuration options and limits on using subprocesses.
fix shebang line
Graphing ruleset trie with graphvia via gvgen (debug feature).
Nicer and more easily greppable errors when using subprocesses
Leftmost wildcard in 'target' ruleset element will match arbitrary number of domains, if it's at least 3-rd level. Support for test URL lists.

An exclusion need not be anchored to the start of a URL!

The exclusion should apply if the exclusion pattern matches anywhere
within the URL.
package https-everywhere-checker for PyPI
Less strict dependencies
Fix invocation of subprocess fetch after files have changed namespaces
Remove executable flag
Documentation
Keep tox.ini dependencies on par with setup.py deps
Add coverage checking.
Tweak certdir for use in testing.
Add support for automatically disabling rules.

Break out purpose-specific configs into own files.

And restore sample checker config.

Auto disabling and cipher suite options.

Add ability for check_rules to automatically disable rules that fail HTTP fetch.
Also split out configs for various use cases.
Also add a config option for cipher suites to use.
Allow http disabling, account for non-capturing groups.
Enable http by default for manual checking.
Comment config files.
Remove stray print statement.
Fix rulesdir for manual and disable checker configs.
Improve handling of parse errors in XML.
Fixed some errors
Add skiplist support for whitelist hashes.
Add cookie jar support and shorter logging.
json output added
coverage checks added to json
logic fix
regex error handling
Added ErrorSanitizer to handle TLS and network errors
Misc improvements to ruleset checker.

Stop including rules in problem statements.

This caused interpolation problems when putting the problem statements into
disabled rulesets, because they contained group backreferences.
Headers are case insensitive.
Don't parse identical documents.
Use 40 threads for disable-broken-rulesets.

Ignore escaped question marks

When counting required test URLs.
Bump log level for manual checker to INFO.

Use COOKEFILE and COOKIEJAR.

Both are required: one for reading, one for writing.

Update platform_certs and fix bugs.

Bug fixes are mostly triggered by
https://github.com/EFForg/https-everywhere/pull/1201

Improve checker configs

Fewer threads for disable-broken-rulesets, reduces spurious timeouts.
Use Mozilla user-agent to mitigate user-agent-specific issues, in particular for
CDG_Commerce (but probably affects other rulesets).
Remove exception logging.
Fix string formatting in coverage reports
Add Gandi Standard SSL CA 2.
Add lxml as a requirement.
Add a get-issuer.sh to fetch missing intermediates
Check_rules shouldn't fail if HTTP version fails.
Remove lxml from requirements.txt
Disable coverage_check in sample config, because it breaks IDNA domains.
